## You can add one or more bridges. Bridges are a way to communicate with the
## Host side from your target hardware design. For example, you can use UART bridge
## and interact with your design by running 'screen tty/xxx 115200' on the host
## where the simulation is running. You will need a working UART hardware
## implementation of UART in your design, and then you can connect
## the UART ports of your design to the UART bridge here.
## Other bridges support RAM access, Virtual BlockDevice access etc.
## Use the port_map section to map the port key name from the design section above
## as values in this section. The port key names must be as specified in the bridge.
## Check specific bridge documentation for details on port key names to use.
## OPTIONAL: You can leave/delete this section if your designs dont require bridnges.

